results.title: The Hunger Part 3
results.description: Spidey lets Garrett know that he believes the Venom suit is attacking people and sucking their adrenaline because it is looking for a new host; May implements her plan to move the still vegetative Flash Thompson into an apartment in Peter's complex; Venom and Brock, together again, hunt down Spidey; Spider-Man realizes, far too late, that the new host the symbiotic suit is craving is him.

results.title: The Hunger Part 4
results.description: Spidey battles to keep the Venom suit from possessing him with a little help from his buddies in the F.F.; The plan is a success but the suit escapes; Garrett receives a heartfelt letter from the tortured Eddie Brock; Spidey tracks down Brock and learns why the suit has given up on its former host.

results.title: Pulsating Premiere Issue!  The Cosmic Avenger -- Now In His Own Book!  Featuring... The Untold Origin of Quasar!
The Price Of Power
results.description: Wendell Vaughan is temporarily assigned to the S.H.I.E.L.D. security detail guarding his father's investigation of the alien Quantum-Bands.  A.I.M. attempts to steal them, but Wendell dons the Bands and single-handedly repulses the A.I.M. attack.

results.title: By The Time I Get To Phoenix
To Learn His Cosmic Destiny From Eon -- -- Quasar Must First Survive A Deadly Duel With… Deathurge!
Destiny Amidst The Ruins
results.description: Depressed, Quasar undertakes a dangerous trip to Uranus to discover the origins of the Quantum-Bands.  In suspended animation for the 3-year trip, Wendell awakens to confront Deathurge and is chosen by Eon to be Protector of the Universe.
